<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1129693374"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1126788409"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1045330069"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1129693374"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1129693374"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1129693374"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1129693374"><table class="sidebar nomobile nowraplinks"><tbody><tr><td class="sidebar-pretitle" style="background-color:#D4AF37; color:#f7f1e3;">Part of a series on the</td></tr><tr><th class="sidebar-title-with-pretitle" style="background-color:#D4AF37;"><a class="mw-selflink selflink"><span style="color:#f7f1e3;">Guru Granth Sahib<br />ਗੁਰੂ ਗ੍ਰੰਥ ਸਾਹਿਬ</span></a></th></tr><tr><td class="sidebar-image" style="background-color:#D4AF37;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Guru_Granth_Sahib_manuscript_housed_at_Sri_Keshgarh_Sahib,_Anandpur_and_dated_to_1803_B.S._(1746_C.E.)_beautifully_decorated_with_gold_and_floral_arabesques_01.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Guru_Granth_Sahib_manuscript_housed_at_Sri_Keshgarh_Sahib%2C_Anandpur_and_dated_to_1803_B.S._%281746_C.E.%29_beautifully_decorated_with_gold_and_floral_arabesques_01.jpg/250px-thumbnail.jpg" decoding="async" width="250" height="163" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Guru_Granth_Sahib_manuscript_housed_at_Sri_Keshgarh_Sahib%2C_Anandpur_and_dated_to_1803_B.S._%281746_C.E.%29_beautifully_decorated_with_gold_and_floral_arabesques_01.jpg/375px-thumbnail.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Guru_Granth_Sahib_manuscript_housed_at_Sri_Keshgarh_Sahib%2C_Anandpur_and_dated_to_1803_B.S._%281746_C.E.%29_beautifully_decora